1,1072568158153,2024-07-25T19:38:38.039Z,"One Ministries, Inc.",,,"July 25, 2024
Marlene H. Dortch, Esq.
Secretary Federal Communications Commission
45 L Street NE Washington DC 20554
Re: MB Docket No. 24-211,
Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements
Dear Ms. Dortch:
In the NPRM, the FCC asks for comment on the following statement:
“We tentatively conclude that the same public interest justifications that support the proposed rules for
broadcast stations apply equally to cable operators, DBS providers, and SDARS licensees engaged in
origination programming. We seek comment on this tentative conclusion.”
One Ministries, Inc. (OMI) requests that for the purposes of this NRPM that the definition of cable
operators also include vMVPD operators such as YouTube TV, Hulu Plus Live TV, Sling TV, Fubo TV,
Peacock Premium Plus and DirecTV Stream. YouTube TV is projected to soon have a subscriber base
larger than any other cable or DBS provider. Therefore, it would be prudent to consider YouTube TV to
be a cable operator as well as any streaming service that carries at least one local broadcast station in a
television market. Regarding the authority that the Commission has to include vMPVDs as cable
systems for the purpose of the NPRM, please refer to pages 3 and 4 of the comments submitted by the
Competitive Enterprise Institute, The International Center for Law & Economics, and TechFreedom filed
March 3, 2015.1
Sincerely,
Keith J. Leitch
President, One Ministries, Inc. (KQSL)
1 Comments of the Competitive Enterprise Institute, The International Center for Law & Economics, and
TechFreedom dated March 13, 2015 on pages 3 and 4:
