Dear Commissioners,

I’m writing to express my support for the FCC’s proposed rule No. 24-211. Specifically the provision dictating the disclosure of AI-generated content in political communications. Measures like these are essential for transparency and protecting the democratic process. 

A functioning democracy only works with a trustworthy information ecosystem at the helm. When voters are unsure if they can trust information fed to them it undermines their ability to make an informed decision which can effect the overall democratic process potentially leading to lower voter turnout. AI-Generated content without transparency erodes public confidence, leads to distrust of all information and potentially voter apathy. By establishing strong regulations for disclosing AI in political ads, this ensures a more transparent information ecosystem. 

I support the follow aspects of the proposed rules: 
On-Air and Written Disclosures: When it comes to deepfakes and other AI-generated content, I favor requiring both on-air and written disclosures on political advertisements. 
Requiring These Disclosure For Both Candidates & Issue Ads: Both candidates and issues should be subject to the same transparency standards to ensure voters know what is AI and what isn’t. 
Includes Broadcasters and Other Entities: Establishing these disclosure requirements for all content carriers ensures that content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered; including federal, state, and local levels. 

Each of these measures have the potential to protect voters from deceptive ads & enhance transparency. I strongly urge the commission to adopt these rules. Please continue these efforts to safeguard election integrity as world continues to technologically advance. 

Regards,
Alyssa Arroyo
