268,10823948829739,2024-08-23T16:57:11.885Z,Julie Bernstein,,,"Dear Commissioners, 
I strongly support the Federal Communications Commission’s proposed rulemaking No. 24-211. The provisions concerning the disclosure of AI-generated content in political communications are urgently needed because we have already seen AI- generated miscommunication this election cycle when someone created a fake robo-call communication with President Biden’s voice urging New Hampshire voters not to vote in the primary(https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2024-election/fake-joe-biden-robocall-tells-new-hampshire-democrats-not-vote-tuesday-rcna134984?link_id=2&can_id=307f3beb18b704c1c016d36c46d3a2f6&source=email-help-stop-deceptive-ai-in-political-ads&email_referrer=email_24). The measures that you are considering are essential to ensuring transparency so that voters are not misinformed and are attune to accurate information as opposed to being misled about candidates and potentially even disenfranchised. 
It is important to consider the full implications of allowing AI-adulterated information to be circulated. When voters have doubts about the veracity of information that they hear or see, they will start ignoring all of it. To preserve a healthy and democratic election process, it is thus urgent that all political ads disclose whether AI is being used.
I support the following aspects of the proposed rules: 
On-Air and Written Disclosure Requirements: On-air disclosures and written disclosures of AI-generated content should be mandatory whenever it is used in broadcasters’ political files especially when deepfakes are employed. 
Application to Both Candidate and Issue Advertisements: The disclosure requirements should apply to both candidate and issue advertisements because of the broad impact of AI-generated content and the fact that for most voters issues, whether in the context of a ballot initiative or as part of a candidate’s platform, are the basis for decision-making in an election. 
Inclusive Application to Broadcasters and Other Entities:  The disclosure requirements must be applicable to all pertinent content carriers so that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered at the local, state, and federal levels. Fake information is destructive at every level and for many people, local decisions, for example about who will serve on their local Board of Education, have a profound impact on daily life for them and their children.
Your proposed measures to enhance transparency and protect voters from deceptive practices are essential to protecting our democracy. Please adopt these rules and continue rule-making that is vital to safeguarding the integrity of our elections in the face of ever more complex and abstruse technology which the public is increasingly unable to trust for its fidelity to the truth.
Sincerely, 
Julie Bernstein",2824
