491,10824410810282,2024-08-24T00:01:49.107Z,Jody MacDonald,,,"Federal Communications Commission
45 12th Street SW
Washington, D.C. 20554

Dear Commissioners,

I am writing to express my strong support for the Federal Communications Commission’s proposed rulemaking
No. 24-211, in particular, provisions concerning the disclosure of AI-generated content in political
communications. We must have these measures to ensure transparency and protection of our
democratic processes.

AI, misused, is extremely dangerous, particularly in the political arena, where even more aware/informed people can be fooled by professionally done false AI “information.” I worry for our country, and our democratic process in the face of AI generated political ads and misinformation campaigns. It’s hard to have an informed conversation with anyone, when no one can trust the information put “out there.” It erodes trust in our own beliefs, and serves no good purpose, but rather, pulls people apart from one another. It is a danger that, when masked as “reality,” threatens the very fabric of our society.

I support the following aspects of the proposed rules:

On-Air and Written Disclosure Requirements: We favor requiring both on-air disclosures and written
disclosures in broadcasters’ political files when AI-generated content is used, especially to create deceptive
deepfakes.

Application to Both Candidate and Issue Advertisements: Extending the disclosure requirements to both
candidate and issue advertisements recognizes the broad impact of AI-generated content and ensures that
all political messaging is subject to the same transparency standards.

Inclusive Application to Broadcasters and Other Entities: Applying the disclosure requirements to all
pertinent content carriers ensures that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered
at the local, state, and federal levels.

I believe that these measures could help protect voters from deceptive practices and enhance transparency. I ask
the commission to, please, adopt these rules and continue your efforts to safeguard our elections in
the face of rapidly evolving technological challenges and threats.

Thank you!

Sincerely,
(Ms.) Jody MacDonald",2161
