567,10824992515446,2024-08-24T00:54:48.539Z,John J. White,,,"The use of AI is becoming prevalent and will become ubiquitous in broadcast media and in on-line social media.


I support an outright ban.  Given that First Amendment provides the right of free speech, does that right include deliberately (or not deliberately) false information, false audio and false images?  I say ""no,"" although I am not a student of constitutional law.


At the very least, there should be a message in front of such AI-generation text, audio and/or image, in large text font size or in loud audio, that explains that AI content, which may be untrue, follows.  Further, that message should be evident for a minimum of 30 seconds--if not longer.


As one citizen, I depend on the FCC to defend the public against misinformation--from foreign actors or from other citizens or corporations.",809
