1336,10829101015967,2024-08-29T16:08:17.480Z,Jeff Kronick,,,"I strongly support the FCC's proposal to regulate deepfakes and AI, to create more clarity and understanding for listeners and viewers of content, especially when it comes to our elections.

Americans must not be subjected to outright lies and disinformation in connection with our elections.  Deepfakes and AI posts and advertisements on the internet and other media are insidious, and persistently dishonest representations of candidates, their records, and their views.  As such, they have pernicious and corrosive effects on American democracy and on how Americans consider their elective choices.  

Regulating these forms of online content is essential to an American democracy where truth reigns over lies and deceit.  Please make these regulations comprehensive, and faithful to a democratic society which needs all the help it can get now to be sustained, and to thrive.",879
1337,10829058700401,2024-08-29T16:08:48.232Z,Susan Bunsick,,,"I'm writing in support of this proposal.  Deep fakes and AI-generated images and text present many societal challenges.  In  particular, they  have no place in a democratic society    in which citizens must rely on accurate information and representations about candidates they choose for offices at all levels of government.  At a minimum, any use of deep fakes and AI-generated text and images need to be clearly identified as such.  This would complement existing requirements with respect to candidate endorsements of political ads and financial disclosure.",561
