1685,10903630317389,2024-09-03T14:14:04.793Z,Laurie Neagle,,,"Federal Communications Commission
45 12th Street SW
Washington, D.C. 20554

Dear Commissioners,

I write to express my strong support for the Federal Communications Commission’s proposed rulemaking
No. 24-211, particularly the provisions concerning the disclosure of AI-generated content in political
communications. These measures are essential to ensuring transparency and protecting the integrity of our
democratic processes. There should never be AI Generated content that creates fakes of political opponents, 
creating lies and division.

A trustworthy information ecosystem is the bedrock of a functioning democracy: If voters are unsure
whether they can trust the information in front of them, it undermines informed decision-making and the
overall health of our democratic processes. The lack of transparency and Unethical behavior in AI-generated 
content can erode public confidence, potentially leading to voter apathy and distrust of all information,
 regardless of its veracity. Establishing strong regulations for disclosing AI in political ads is the first step 
towards ensuring a robust information ecosystem in the wake of these new capabilities.
I support the following aspects of the proposed rules:

On-Air and Written Disclosure Requirements: We favor requiring both on-air disclosures and written
disclosures in broadcasters’ political files when AI-generated content is used, especially to create deceptive
deepfakes.

Application to Both Candidate and Issue Advertisements: Extending the disclosure requirements to both
candidate and issue advertisements recognizes the broad impact of AI-generated content and ensures that
all political messaging is subject to the same transparency standards.

Inclusive Application to Broadcasters and Other Entities: Applying the disclosure requirements to all
pertinent content carriers ensures that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered
at the local, state, and federal levels.

I believe that these measures could enhance transparency and protect voters from deceptive practices. I urge
the commission to adopt these rules and to continue its efforts to safeguard the integrity of our elections in
the face of rapidly evolving technological challenges.

Sincerely,
Mrs. Laurie Neagle",2280
1686,109030049105759,2024-09-03T14:28:58.977Z,Nancy Campbell,,,"Federal Communications Commission
45 12th Street SW
Washington, D.C. 20554

Dear Commissioners,

I STRONGLY SUPPORT the Federal Communications Commission’s proposed rulemaking
No. 24-211!   Especially the provisions about disclosure of AI-generated content in political
communications. 

These measures are absolutely ESSENTIAL!  They ensure transparency.  They protect the integrity of our democratic processes.  They ensure that we Americans can TRUST our political information!

Our information “ecosystem” MUST BE TRUSTWORTHY or our democracy will descend into chaos – a chaos we are just beginning to see and experience!   

Trust in the information that floods us every day is the bedrock of a functioning democracy!  If we voters are unsure if we can trust the information in front of us, it undermines everything we do.  There will be no more informed decision-making.  The health of our democratic processes will fail.  Propaganda and private agendas will prevail – they will literally rule us!  Propagandists will have succeeded in destroying democracy by taking control of the information system!

The total lack of transparency in AI-generated content destroys public confidence.  

And that leads to disaster -- voter apathy and distrust of all information regardless of its truth. 

WE MUST ESTABLISH STRONG REGULATIONS for disclosing AI in political ads!!

It is the first step towards being sure we continue to have a robust and TRUTHFUL information ecosystem in the wake of this new technology!

I support the following aspects of the proposed rules:

On-Air and Written Disclosure Requirements:  Require both on-air disclosures and written
disclosures in broadcasters’ political files when AI-generated content is used, especially to create deceptive deepfakes.  STOP THE DECEPTION!!

Application to Both Candidate and Issue Advertisements: Extend disclosure requirements to both candidate and issue advertisements.  This recognizes the huge impact of AI-generated content.  It  ensures all political messaging is subject to the same transparency standards.

Inclusive Application to Broadcasters and Other Entities: Apply the disclosure requirements to all
pertinent content carriers.  This ensures that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered at the local, state, and federal levels.

These are strong first steps!  They will enhance transparency and protect voters from deceptive practices.  

Deceit and deception are democracy-killers, and you have the power to stop a lot of it!

I URGE YOU!  ADOPT THESE RULES!

Continue your efforts to protect the integrity of our elections in the face of rapidly-evolving technology!

Regards,
Nancy Campbell
Kansas City MO 64112
Nancy.campbell@leaderfuelnow.com",2752
1687,10903202968631,2024-09-03T14:45:07.059Z,Karl Christopher,,,"FCC 24-211 Comment

Federal Communications Commission
45 12th Street SW
Washington, D.C. 20554

Good morning Commissioners,
I am reaching out to your office today to express my FULL support for the Federal Communications Commission’s proposed rulemaking No. 24-211, particularly the provisions concerning the disclosure of AI-generated content in political communications. 

These proposed measures are a MUST HAVE to ensuring transparency and protecting the integrity of our fragile Democracy, and that of all our democratic processes.
TRUST is the only bedrock of a well-functioning democracy: If voters are unsure whether they can trust the information in front of them, it undermines informed decision-making and the overall health of our democratic processes. 

AI-generated content is already being weaponized to erode public confidence, misinform & misdirect the public actions en masse. Information distrust is a seed, and AI is planting those seeds everywhere, at a rate that Legislation cannot keep up with.

Establishing strong regulations for disclosing AI in political ads is a MUST HAVE.

With these thoughts in mind, I strongly support the following aspects of the proposed rules:
On-Air and Written Disclosure Requirements: We favor requiring both on-air disclosures and written disclosures in broadcasters’ political files when AI-generated content is used, especially to create ANY and ALL “deepfakes”.

Application to Both Candidate and Issue Advertisements: Extending the disclosure requirements to both candidate and issue advertisements recognizes the broad impact of AI-generated content and ensures that all political messaging is subject to the same transparency standards.

Inclusive Application to Broadcasters and Other Entities: Applying the disclosure requirements to all pertinent content carriers ensures that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are covered at the local, state, and federal levels.

I believe that these measures could enhance transparency and protect voters from deceptive practices. I urge the commission to adopt these rules, and to *continue* its efforts to safeguard the integrity of fairness, transparency, and clarity of our democratic elections
in the face of rapidly evolving technological advancements coupled with ever-present threats by domestic & foreign bad actors.

Thank you for your consideration of my comments.",2399
