1696,10903018627147,2024-09-03T16:45:19.609Z,Bruce Lott,,,"Federal Communications Commission
45 12th Street SW
Washington, D.C. 20554
Dear Commissioners,
I want to express my strong support for the FCC’s proposed rulemaking No. 24-211, especially the
provisions concerning the disclosure of AI-generated content in political communications. These
provisions are critical to ensure transparency and to protect the integrity of our democratic processes,
particularly our elections.
AI-generated content is becoming harder and harder to distinguish from genuine content, and has
already been used to spread election disinformation. Ordinary citizens do not have sophisticated tools
necessary to determine the veracity of such content, and could be misled about candidates’ statements
or positions, election issues, and voting procedures. This is a threat to our democracy!
The following aspects of the proposed rules are particularly important to me:
• Obvious and clear on-air disclosures and written disclosures in broadcasters’ political files must
be required when AI-generated content is used (especially to create deceptive deepfakes).
• The disclosure requirements must apply to both candidate and issue advertisements, due to the
broad impact of AI-generated content. This ensures that all political messaging is subject to the
same transparency standards.
• The disclosure requirements must apply to all pertinent content carriers (including broadcasters
and other entities), to ensure that all major content platforms under the FCC’s jurisdiction are
covered at the local, state, and federal levels.
I believe that these measures will improve transparency and protect voters from deceptive practices,
and request that the Commission adopt these rules. Please continue your efforts to protect the integrity
of our elections!
Sincerely,
Bruce Lott",1793
