II. WHYTHIS MATTERS FOR LATINOS
The issue of disclosure of the use of artificial intelligence (AI) inpolitical advertisingis
particularly important to the Latino community, which is one of the fastest-growing and most
diverse populations in the United States. According to a Pew Research Center analysis, Latinos
have grown at the second-fastest rate, behind Asian Americans, of any major racial and ethnic
group in the U.S. since the last presidential election, and are projected to account for 14.7
percent, or 36.2 million, of all eligible voters in November 2024, a new high.3 Thepowerof AI
can enhance the political experiences of the Latino community. AI-generated content can offer
significant benefits in political advertising. This can be beneficial for reaching specific
audiences, including the Latino community, through targeted messaging in Spanish and other
languages , and empowering less-resourced campaigns.4 However, Latinos are also uniquely
vulnerable totheharms posedbyAI-generated content,includingAI-generatedpolitical content.
The Latino community'svulnerability toAI-generatedcontentstems fromseveral factors.
Many Latinos primarily consume newsinSpanish, whichhasbeen atargetfor information fraud
campaigns in recent years.5 The widespread use of Spanish-language disinformation has shown
how information fraud can spread, leading to confusion, mistrust, and disengagement from the
political process.6 AI-generated content, particularly when used in political advertisements, has
the potential to exacerbate theseissuesbymaking itmoredifficult for votersto discernfactfrom
