103 Linos and Carlson, supra note 101.
104 See Id. at 217 (“Many doctrinal research projects suffer from selection bias… [s]ampling methods are
particularly helpful for these projects and allow legal scholars to generalize beyond the specific cases they
analyze in depth.”).
