3.8 Ethics and Positionality
This project was approved by an IREC form. CUREC was deemed unnecessary because
the hearings are already public, take place in a public forum, and constitute public records.
Legislators and public testifiers were aware and conscious of the public nature of their
comments, reducing privacy concerns. Since standard practice in legal proceedings is to name
the sponsor and the person speaking on a bill, I did not withhold names or anonymize
legislators. Finally, public figures have lower privacy rights, especially regarding the use of
their public statements.129
Additionally, I note my positionality with respect to the data, which legal scholarship is
unconcerned with. I am not a lawyer; I am an outsider to the legal process and legal
arguments. However, my background and prior legal work experience familiarized me with
legal processes and vocabulary which surfaced in hearings.
