SOC. SCI. 243 (2023) (investigating election subversion policies). In a series of papers, an interdisciplinary team
at the University of Washington tracked the spread of COVID-19 policies and found it aligned with partisanship.
See e.g. Christopher Adolph et al., Pandemic Politics: Timing State-Level Social Distancing Responses to
