1780,1091873507721,2024-09-18T16:33:33.842Z,Benjamin Ben-Baruch,,,"AI needs to be strongly regulated.  AI in political advertising needs to be either banned entirely or VERY strongly controlled and regulated.  I would very much prefer a stronger proposal than that now being considered by the FCC.  Nevertheless I urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible.  This is the absolute minimum that the FCC should be doing.

Given recent advances in artificial intelligence, I’m concerned that candidates and issue campaigners will have an open invitation to deceive voters unless you step in. High quality deepfakes can realistically depict people saying or doing things that did not occur. By requiring a clear disclosure every time AI is used to make an ad, you will be taking a step to prevent political actors from deceiving the public.

