1848,10918962211408,2024-09-18T17:01:42.672Z,Bruce Tsutsui,,,"I am writing this to urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible.

I am very concerned that certain parties that may not have public welfare in mind, including (but not limited to) political candidates, issue campaigners, and large corporations will look at the recent advances in Artificial Intelligence (AI) as an open invitation to deceive voters unless you step in. AI-created ads can generate images of people saying things or events that did not occur and/or distort what actually was said or happened. This is already happening and no one that is paying attention can doubt that these attempts will only increase. By requiring a clear disclosure every time AI is used to make an ad AND having an effective enforcement tool to penalize those that want to disguise it, the FCC can prevent political actors from deceiving the public and help restore trust in the political process and government function. 

The FCC proposal is a needed step to ensure clarity and transparency and help restore the integrity of our democratic process. Please adopt it without delay. Thanks very much.",1206
