1924,109180429625121,2024-09-18T17:52:01.359Z,Chris McNamara,,,"""I urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible.

Given recent advances in artificial intelligence, I’m concerned that candidates and issue campaigners will have an open invitation to deceive voters unless you step in. High quality deepfakes can realistically depict people saying or doing things that did not occur. By requiring a clear disclosure every time AI is used to make an ad, you can prevent political actors from deceiving the public.

This is even more important, given the electorate’s overall suspicions of what is and is not real. A Democracy cannot stand if a significant portion of its Citizens are unable to tell if something is real or not. This has already led to violence. 

In my daily life I’ve encountered people who swear by some deepfakes that are clearly false. 

It is unlawful for a person to fraudulently represent themselves for real gain, go to jail. In this, candidates and political entities have everything to gain by creating a believed deepfake that fits what they want and even some of the best intentioned people just want to know what is and is not real. They are obvious to me, but AI is getting better by the day, and its growth is exponential.

Legibly labeling this content protects free speech of the…”artist” and the right of individuals to not hear someone yell fire in a crowded theater, with flame and heat effects to match. 

Further, without this measure, foreign actors and enemies can creat such content for their own benefits, deliberately manipulating the American People.

Your proposal is a strong step to ensure transparency and the integrity of our democratic process. Please adopt it without delay. 

Then we can worry about AI weaponization for bullying, personal vendettas and on and on the harms that could be done. 

The audience is always told if it’s a movie, if it’s based on true, or if it’s documentary. These sorts of distinctions are essential to both the rights and freedoms of all Americans, but also to not further weaken our Democratic Republic. 
Thank you for your time.""",2165
