2026,10918926014928,2024-09-18T20:56:09.097Z,David Williams,,,"Isaac Asimov proposed Three Laws of Robotics in an attempt to limit the potential damage from artificial beings (I, ROBOT.  1950).  Those principles need to be applied to Artificial Intelligence for the same reason.  
1.	A robot may not injure a human being, or, through inaction, allow a human being to come to harm.
2.	A robot must obey orders given it by human beings except where such orders would conflict with the First Law.
3.	A robot must protect its own existence as long as such protection does not conflict with the First or Second Law.

Political lies have been around as long as politics, but were often readily discernable.  Artificial Intelligence is becoming very good at generating lies in the form of audio and visual images that require very sophisticated means to identify as fakes, leaving most casual viewers unaware they’re being scammed.  This has got to be halted while we have the chance.",914
2027,10918335123626,2024-09-18T20:57:10.926Z,Jacob Huskey,,,"I urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible.

Given recent advances in artificial intelligence, I’m concerned that candidates and issue campaigners will have an open invitation to deceive voters unless you step in. High quality deepfakes can realistically depict people saying or doing things that did not occur. By requiring a clear disclosure every time AI is used to make an ad, you can prevent political actors from deceiving the public.

Your proposal is a strong step to ensure transparency and the integrity of our democratic process. Please adopt it without delay. Thank you for your time.",718
