precise standard does not matter because the mandate would fail any level of First Amendment
scrutiny.30
3. The AI-Disclosure Proposal Would Fail Any Level of Scrutiny.
The Commission’s proposed mandate runs afoul of the First Amendment because it lacks
an important, legitimate interest, and the Commission has failed to tailor its approach to the
interests it purports to advance.
To start, the Commission lacks any legitimate interest—let alone an important one. The
primary interest advanced by the Commission is “providing greater transparency regarding the
use of AI-generated content in political advertising.”31 But that will not do. The “interest at stake
must be more than the satisfaction of mere ‘consumer curiosity.’”32 As then-Judge Kavanaugh
explained in 2014, it is “not enough for the Government to say simply that it has a substantial
