the FEC with exclusive responsibility to “administer, seek to obtain compliance with, and formulate policy
with respect to” FECA); see also, e.g., FEC v. NRA Political Victory Fund, 513 U.S. 88, 91 (1994) (noting
FEC’s authority to ‘“formulate policy’ with respect to [FECA]”); FEC v. Democratic Senatorial Campaign
Comm., 454 U.S. 27, 37 (1981) (noting “Congress has vested the [FEC] with ‘primary and substantial
responsibility for administering and enforcing [FECA]’” (citation omitted)). Cf. Statement of Chairwoman
