2291,10924137713252,2024-09-24T12:18:34.468Z,James Zukowski,,,"I've been in the computer industry for nearly 5 decades, and seen it go through many growing pains. The latest is the wave of ""Artificial Intelligence"" (AI) that is sweeping through the industry. Hardly a day goes by that I don't get an invitation to inject AI into my development process. The problem, though, is that it's far from intelligent. Intelligence includes a conscience, which computer programs simply don't have.
There are many who use this tool - and AI is a TOOL - as a means to an artificial end. The video and gaming industry has used various software tools to change the look and feel of their environments for decades. Now, it's as if it's been put on steroids, and is being used for nefarious purposes: false political advertising. The recent advertisement showing Taylor Swift purportedly endorsing Donald Trump is just one example.
Permitting these deceptions to pollute the minds of the voters is unconscionable. Truth in advertising - especially when it comes to who is to represent us in the halls of power and politics - is of paramount importance. The FCC used to have a ""Fairness Doctrine"" which allowed opposing views to by presented on a (pretty much) equal footing, using real people.
We need to keep the spirit of honesty and truth alive in this country, particularly in politics. That is why I urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible. Your proposal is a strong step to ensure transparency and the integrity of our democratic process. Please adopt it without delay.
Thank you for your time and consideration.",1662
2292,1092416592542,2024-09-24T14:07:41.426Z,Michael Arones,,,"I urge the FCC to adopt its proposal on the Disclosure and Transparency of Artificial Intelligence-Generated Content in Political Advertisements as soon as possible.

The rapid advances in the ability of AI software to almost effortlessly create deep fakes of photographs/video and audio recordings threaten the ability of citizens to know what is real. 
Lies have always been propagated for nefarious purposes, but one used to be able to tell someone to trust their own eyes & ears (including distributed audio/visual recordings) ; with deep fakes, that is no longer the case. 
It allows unethical person & organizations to to mislead Americans to believe in a false alternate reality, in the service of political & monetary gain. 

In particular, deep fakes are being used to lie about the issues and to lie about candidates in our elections. 
Our Democracy is based upon having an informed electorate; but realist AI-generated deep fakes threatens the ability of voters to know the truth.

 By requiring a clear disclosure every time AI is used to make an ad, you can prevent political actors from deceiving the public.

Your proposal is a strong step to ensure transparency and the integrity of our democratic process. 
Please adopt it as soon as possible. 

Thank you for paying attention to my support for this proposal.",1326
